Abstract: New York Times corrects error made in 1898 when the issue succeeding 14,499 was given as 15,000 instead of 14,500 (S)
Snippet: New York Times corrects error made in 1898 when the issue succeeding 14,499 was given as 15,000 instead of 14,500 (S)
LeadParagraph: For those who believe that in the good old days -- before calculators, before computers -- people were better at mental arithmetic, The Times offers a sobering New Year's message: Not necessarily.
